Scott Keyes , a 28-year-old writer for Think Progress , is about to travel 20,000miles on 21 flights  . 
  Along the way he will be stopping by 13 countries in Europe and South and North America while enjoying first class service . 
  He used his frequent flyer miles and points from his 25 credit cards to plan the trip . 
  He will stop in Mexico, Nicaragua, Trinidad, Grenada, Germany and the Czech Republic . 
  Keyes spent between 10 and 15 hours planning the trip and it will cost him 136,500 miles . 
 